The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, May 18: The government today modified the tax deduction 

norms to simplify the quarterly TDS statement used for tax deduction at source 

from ?salaries?. According to the amended rules, there will be only two Annexures 

to the TDS form (Form no 24Q) against the existing three annexures. While Annexure-I 

will be required to be furnished with each quarterly statement containing details 

relevant to the quarter, the modified Annexure-II will be required to be furnished 

with the last quarterly statement of the financial year containing details for 

the whole of the financial year.

 New Delhi, May 18: Indian agricultural and marine products are 

likely to become cheaper in the overseas market once the government notifies the 

abolition of the designated export cess on Monday. These goods comprise 10 per 

cent of the total export basket and are valued at $10 billion.

 Calcutta, May 18: The Calcutta Stock Exchange today signed up PricewaterhouseCoopers 

as adviser to complete the process of demutualisation, CSE secretary P.K. Ray 

said. The agreement was signed by Ray and PwC?s executive director Arindam Guha.

 New Delhi, May 18: Indian Oil, Bharat Petroleum, Hindustan Petroleum 

and IBP have plans to set up 3,222 new retail outlets in the country during the 

current year, the minister of state for petroleum said today.

 New Delhi, May 18: The government has asked manufacturers of electrical 

appliances to start stamping energy labels on their products on a voluntary basis 

and set a six-month deadline for making these labels mandatory.




